  "prompt": "Are there legal frameworks in place to combat money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several legal frameworks and international efforts to combat money laundering, including:\n\n1. International Frameworks:\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention Against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n\n2. National Legislation:\n- Bank Secrecy Act (United States)\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) regulations\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) requirements\n- Suspicious Activity Reporting (SAR) protocols\n\n3. Key Prevention Strategies:\n- Customer due diligence\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Reporting suspicious financial activities\n- Imposing significant penalties for non-compliance\n\n4. Regulatory Bodies:\n- Financial intelligence units\n- Central banks\n- Law enforcement agencies\n- International cooperation mechanisms\n\n5. Compliance Requirements:\n- Financial institutions must implement robust AML programs\n- Regular employee training\n- Maintaining detailed transaction records\n- Conducting risk assessments\n\nThese frameworks aim to detect, prevent, and prosecute money laundering activities across different jurisdictions and financial sectors.",
